\f2\b \cf2 Use Google Document AI for primary OCR/HTR, OpenAI for extraction/reasoning/synthesis, OpenSearch for exact + hybrid retrieval, PostgreSQL for source-of-truth records, and a mandatory human review queue for uncertainty.
\f1\b0 \
\
That is the best practical stack for your problem right now. Google\'92s Enterprise Document OCR is built for scanned documents, supports handwriting, rotation correction, and page-level quality signals, while OpenAI\'92s file search / vector-store stack is strong for semantic + keyword retrieval over indexed content rather than raw messy scans.  \
\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\sl324\slmult1\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

