\f2\b \cf2 OpenAI is the better LLM layer. It is not the better raw OCR layer.
\f1\b0 \
\
OpenAI\'92s hosted file search is very useful because it provides semantic and keyword search over uploaded files in vector stores, and OpenAI\'92s vector stores support chunking strategies directly. But that helps most 
\f2\b after
\f1\b0  you have usable text or normalized records. It does not replace a handwriting-first document pipeline for old aviation logs.  \
\
Google Document AI is explicitly positioned for document understanding and its Enterprise OCR supports handwriting, deskew/rotation correction, quality scoring, and layout extraction. AWS Textract also supports extracting printed text, handwriting, layout elements, and form/table data.  \
\
So the split is:\
